# Terminology

- Cluster: A bunch of nodes
- Nodes: VMs or physical machines
- Master Node: Manages other nodes and provide interface of cluster to user
- Addons: cluster features like DNS, Web UI, Container Resource
  Monitoring, Cluster level logging

# Components

## Master

- kube-apiserver: api for user or cli
- etcd: key-value store
- kube-scheduler: finds a node for new pods
- kube-controller-manager: includes Node controller, Replication Controller,
  Endpoints Controller, Service Accounts and Token Controllers
- cloud-controller-manager

## Node

- kubelet: an agent on each node
- kube-proxy: maintains network rules
- Container Runtime: any OCI runtime-spec implementation e.g. Docker, rkt, runc
